  "title": "fix(selector): root classname is applied twice",
  "body": "The implementation of the React component `Selector` was applying the `root` css\r\nclasses that were already applied by the headerfooter. In order to\r\nprevent regressions and let user customize the <select>, this patch adds\r\na new key to customize cssClasses in Selector bases widgets (`select`), and this\r\nnew key has the root value to avoid breaking the current implementations.\r\n\r\nFix #2396 #2397",
